==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cha
<hw>Cha</hw> <pr>(ch⟦aum⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Chin.
<ets>ch⟦lsquo⟧a</ets>.]</ety> <altsp>[Also <asp>chaa</asp>,
<asp>chais</asp>, <asp>tsia</asp>, etc.]</altsp> <def>Tea; -- the
Chinese (Mandarin) name, used generally in early works of travel, and
now for a kind of rolled tea used in Central Asia.</def></p>

<p><q>A pot with hot water . . . made with the powder of a certain herb
called <qex>chaa</qex>, which is much esteemed.</q> <rj><qau>Tr. J. Van
Linschoten's Voyages (1598).</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chab</ent>⟦br⟧
